# Keep line endings EXACTLY as committed. The repo is intentionally mixed (some CRLF,
# most LF) with core.autocrlf=false; `-text` tells git never to convert or renormalize,
# so no file changes now and future tooling can't silently flip CRLF<->LF and bury the
# real diff. (If a tool does flip a file, git will show it as a genuine byte change you
# can catch, instead of auto-hiding it.)
* -text

# Tracked binaries: also never diff as text.
*.exe  binary
*.dll  binary
*.pyd  binary
*.zip  binary
*.nif  binary
*.tri  binary
*.osd  binary
*.dds  binary
*.bsa  binary
